# H: Drive Storage Only — C: Is Off Limits

The C: drive is critically full (~1 GB free). **Never write temporary, cache, scratch, or output files to C.**

## Required paths (Block-Street repo on H:)

| Purpose | Path |
|---------|------|
| Temp / scratch | `H:\Block-Street\.tmp` |
| npm cache | `H:\Block-Street\.npm-cache` |
| Tool caches (pip/pnpm/playwright) | `H:\Block-Street\.caches` |
| Agent IDE spill (junctioned) | `H:\Block-Street\.cursor-ide` |
| Build output | `H:\Block-Street\.next` |
| Project files | `H:\Block-Street\` |
| Cursor globalStorage (after relocate) | `H:\CursorData\globalStorage` |

## Shell commands (mandatory every session)

Before any npm, node, tsc, next, pip, pnpm, playwright, or python tool in PowerShell:

```powershell
$env:TEMP = 'H:\Block-Street\.tmp'
$env:TMP = 'H:\Block-Street\.tmp'
$env:TMPDIR = 'H:\Block-Street\.tmp'
$env:npm_config_cache = 'H:\Block-Street\.npm-cache'
$env:npm_config_tmp = 'H:\Block-Street\.tmp'
$env:PIP_CACHE_DIR = 'H:\Block-Street\.caches\pip'
$env:XDG_CACHE_HOME = 'H:\Block-Street\.caches'
$env:PNPM_STORE_DIR = 'H:\Block-Street\.caches\pnpm-store'
$env:PLAYWRIGHT_BROWSERS_PATH = 'H:\Block-Street\.caches\playwright'
```

Prefer: `node scripts/run-with-h-env.mjs <command>` which applies env automatically.

One-time / repair:

```powershell
powershell -File H:\Block-Street\scripts\setup-h-drive-env.ps1
powershell -File H:\Block-Street\scripts\free-c-drive-caches.ps1
```

If C: still screams about free space, Cursor's `state.vscdb` (~20GB) is the culprit. Quit Cursor and run:

```powershell
powershell -File H:\Block-Street\scripts\relocate-cursor-state-to-h.ps1
```

## Forbidden

- Do not use `C:\Users\...\AppData\Local\Temp` for scratch files
- Do not create temp/cache files on `C:\` anywhere
- Do not redirect output to `C:\` paths
- Do not use Travel-Expense or other project temp paths — use `H:\Block-Street\.tmp` only
- Do not leave pip/pnpm/playwright/npm caches on C:

## Scripts

Phase 11 and deployment scripts must `import '../h-drive-env.mjs'` (or `./h-drive-env.mjs`) before spawning child processes.
